flowRoot.flowPara: >1 million pipe-delimited transaction records, released in several text data files
CRS records grouped by title, short description, long description. These groups are called code rules. They were divided by sector into >300 codesheets (.xls).
Project managers assign codesheets to AidData research assistants who read each code rule and assign AidData sector codes. Each codesheet is processed by two coders.

Codesheets are loaded to the data management system behind the AidData.org data portal. When they match, the codes are merged. When they differ, they are reviewed by a senior research who assigns a master code.
Coded and arbitrated records are published on AidData.org and may be viewed and exported from the data potal.
AidData internal software uses code rules to assign sector codes to CRS project records.
Composed in May 2012. Comments or Questions? Contact info@aiddata.org.
